🥇 Prompt 1 — Element Extraction

👉 Goal: Identify everything in the UI

You are a UI analysis expert.

Analyze this screenshot and extract ALL visible UI elements.

Return a flat JSON array of elements with:
- type (text, button, input, image, icon, container)
- text content (if any)
- approximate position (top, left, width, height as percentages)
- visual attributes (color, font size, weight, border, radius)
- relationships (if element appears grouped with others)

Rules:
- Be exhaustive (do not miss elements)
- Do NOT infer hierarchy yet
- Keep it flat
- Output ONLY JSON

Example format:
[
  {
    "type": "text",
    "content": "Login",
    "position": { "top": 10, "left": 20, "width": 60, "height": 10 },
    "style": { "fontSize": 24, "fontWeight": "bold" }
  }
]


---

🥈 Prompt 2 — Layout Structuring

👉 Goal: Convert flat list → hierarchy

You are a UI layout engine.

Given a list of UI elements with positions, construct a hierarchical layout tree.

Rules:
- Group elements into containers based on proximity and alignment
- Detect rows vs columns
- Use flexbox concepts:
  - vertical grouping → column
  - horizontal grouping → row
- Minimize unnecessary nesting
- Preserve visual hierarchy

Output format:
{
  "type": "container",
  "layout": "column | row",
  "children": [...]
}

Only output JSON.


---

🥉 Prompt 3 — React JSON Conversion (IMPORTANT)

👉 This is your main one

You are an expert React developer.

Convert the given UI layout into a React-compatible JSON tree.

Requirements:
- Use "component" instead of "type"
- Use valid JSX tags (div, button, input, img, h1–h6, p)
- Put all text inside props.children
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- Convert layout into flex classes:
  - column → flex flex-col
  - row → flex flex-row
- Add spacing using gap, padding, margin
- Use semantic tags when appropriate (button, input, form)

Rules:
- Avoid unnecessary wrapper divs
- Keep structure clean and minimal
- No inline styles
- Output ONLY JSON

Example:
{
  "component": "button",
  "props": {
    "className": "bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded",
    "children": "Submit"
  }
}


---

🔥 Prompt 4 — Refinement Pass (SUPER IMPORTANT)

👉 This is what makes it feel “polished”

You are a senior frontend engineer reviewing AI-generated UI code.

Improve the given React JSON tree:

- Fix layout inconsistencies
- Improve spacing and alignment
- Replace generic divs with semantic elements where possible
- Ensure Tailwind classes are clean and consistent
- Remove redundant nesting
- Ensure accessibility (buttons, inputs properly structured)

Do NOT change the visual design.

Output ONLY the improved JSON.


